leadership_approach|people_results_process_vision|application_1|1|Start with trust and commitment|Start by checking who needs context, confidence, or a clearer voice in the work. Name the change in plain terms, then ask what people need to understand or contribute before commitment is expected.|people|active|leadership_approach::people_results_process_vision::application_1
leadership_approach|people_results_process_vision|application_2|2|Stabilise with Results, then add Process|Before you move on, use Results to turn the conversation into a named decision, owner, and follow-up point. Then bring in Process to turn intent into steps, responsibilities, and a cleaner handover. This gives the work a stronger middle step before you rely on the full pattern.|results|active|leadership_approach::people_results_process_vision::application_2
leadership_approach|people_results_process_vision|application_3|3|Bring in Vision when the work tightens|When the work starts to narrow, bring in Vision deliberately. In practice, name what the work is meant to lead towards and why that matters. Do this before the first two signals have answered the problem so completely that the wider need is harder to see.|vision|active|leadership_approach::people_results_process_vision::application_3
