leadership_approach|people_results_vision_process|application_2|2|Stabilise with Results, then add Vision|Before you move on, use Results to turn the conversation into a named decision, owner, and follow-up point. Then bring in Vision to connect the immediate task to the reason, consequence, or better option. This gives the work a stronger middle step before you rely on the full pattern.|results|active|leadership_approach::people_results_vision_process::application_2
leadership_approach|people_results_vision_process|application_3|3|Bring in Process when the work tightens|When the work starts to narrow, bring in Process deliberately. In practice, write down the steps, standards, or handovers that need to be clearer. Do this before the first two signals have answered the problem so completely that the wider need is harder to see.|process|active|leadership_approach::people_results_vision_process::application_3
